headlines.description: Tanner Leissner scored 19 points, Josh Hopkins added 13 off the bench, and New Hampshire's reserves helped spark the Wildcats to a 64-61 win over Albany on Saturday in their America East Conference home opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Hampshire holds off Albany 64-61

headlines.description: Jayvon Graves and Jeremy Harris scored 16 apiece and combined to hit seven 3-pointers as Buffalo rolled to an 83-63 win over Ball State on Saturday, snapping the Cardinals' nine-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo snaps Ball State's 9-game win streak

headlines.description: Chris Clemons scored 33 points and Campbell beat Winthrop 88-77 on Saturday in the teams' first meeting since last season's Big South title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemons scores 33 as Campbell tops Winthrop 88-77

headlines.description: Jeff Thomas nailed a 3-pointer in the final seconds as Georgia State took a late lead and held on for a 79-75 win over Arkansas State to even its Sun Belt Conference record on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas late 3 gives Georgia St. 79-75 win over Arkansas St.

headlines.description: Bryson Scott and Kason Harrell combined to score 38 points and Fort Wayne beat Denver on the Pioneers' home court for the fourth time in five games Saturday, posting an 82-63 Summit League victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fort Wayne feels at home in Denver, pummel Pioneers 82-63

headlines.description: Keith Braxton, the Northeast Conference Player of the Week for the second straight week, scored 27 points and Jamaal King matched his output as St. Francis of Pennsylvania beat St. Francis of Brooklyn, 91-87 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Red Flash tops Terriers, 91-87 in St. Francis showdown

headlines.description: Anthony Tarke scored 21 points, capping an early 13-2 rally for the lead and NJIT never lost it, defeating South Carolina Upstate 98-87 on Saturday, winning its first Atlantic Sun Conference opener in the three seasons since joining the conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tarke helps NJIT win first ASun opener, 98-87

headlines.description: Georgie Pacheco-Ortiz led a balanced attack with 14 points and Liberty pulled away for a 60-48 win over Presbyterian on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liberty pulls away for 60-48 win over Presbyterian

headlines.description: Ed Polite Jr. scored a career-high 29 points and Radford beat UNC Asheville 90-70 on Saturday to extend its winning streak to five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Polite scores career-high 29 in Radford's 90-70 victory

headlines.description: Daniel Fowler scored 14 of his 21 points in the final minutes as Furman rallied late to beat Mercer 74-71 on Saturday to remain undefeated in Southern Conference action.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fowler gets hot late to help Furman beat Mercer 74-71

headlines.description: Kevon Harris scored 20 points and Shannon Bogues had 14 and Stephen F. Austin beat Northwestern State 64-56 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen F. Austin dumps Northwestern St. 64-56

headlines.description: Deandre Jones converted a three-point play, hit a 3-pointer and assisted on another in a second overtime period as Central Arkansas rallied to beat Lamar, 100-91 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones shoots Central Arkansas past Lamar in 2OT, 100-91

headlines.description: Alex Peacock's lay-in off an offensive rebound with four seconds to play lifted Texas State to a 57-56 win against Troy on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Peacock's putback sends Texas St. past Troy 57-56

headlines.description: Payton Henson scored 14 points with a career-high 13 rebounds and Vermont beat UMBC 71-56 in its America East Conference home opener on Saturday night for its fourth straight win and 22nd straight win against the Retrievers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vermont beats UMBC 71-56 behind Henson

headlines.description: J.D. Notae scored 25 points, Jalyn Hinton had 22, including the clinching free throws with 12 seconds left, and Jacksonville defeated North Florida 90-86 in the River City Rumble to open Atlantic Sun play on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notae, Hinton rally Jacksonville past N Florida 90-86

headlines.description: Demetirus Denzel-Dyson scored 21 points and Triston Chambers nailed five from long range for 15 as Samford dominated Western Carolina 85-71 in Southern Conference action on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Samford dominates W. Carolina 85-71 in Southern Conf. play

headlines.description: Roddy Peters scored 18 of his 24 points in the second half, including two free throws with 21 seconds left, to help Nicholls beat Houston Baptist 72-71 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Peters hits late FTs to help Nicholls beat Houston Baptist

headlines.description: Jonathan Stark scored 22 points and reached the 1,000-point mark for his career as Murray State beat UT Martin 84-66 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stark reaches 1,000; Murray State beats UT Martin 84-66

headlines.description: Jerrick Harding tied a career-high with 31 points and Zach Braxton finished with 22 points and 13 rebounds and Weber State beat Southern Utah 92-76 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harding, Braxton pace Weber St. past S. Utah 92-76

headlines.description: Deontae North scored 30 points and Holland Woods got the winning putback to lift Portland State to a 73-72 win over Idaho on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portland State edges Idaho 73-72 with last-second put-back

headlines.description: Kyle Allman scored eight of his 30 points in overtime and Cal State Fullerton survived Cal Poly's late rally for a 101-97 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: CS Fullerton survives Cal Poly's rally, wins 101-97 in OT

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
